    <thetext>Description of problem:
With Xorg 1.18, my Wacom touchpad honors the tap to click setting of the mouse and touchpad settings menu, but with Xorg 1.19 it doesn&apos;t.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
xorg-x11-drv-wacom.x86_64 version 0.33.0-2.20160929gitb61d1711.fc25
xorg-x11-server-Xorg version 1.19.0-0.2.20160929.fc25

How reproducible:
100%

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Disable tap to click in settings
2. Enable Wacom touchpad (available on some models)
3. Wacom ignores setting and clicks on tap

Actual results:
Wacom ignores setting and clicks on tap.

Expected results:
Wacom honors tap to click setting like it was before (Xorg 1.18).

Additional info:
My current workaround is downgrading Xorg and its dependencies to the Fedora 24 version, which work as expected.</thetext>
